

1) We will be Differentiating "Row Number", "RANK" & "DENSE RANK" 




A) Row Number - [In This there is a Different Row Number which is Assign to the Records Which have Same Salary Like "shane" & "rahul" Both have Salary 20000 but have a Row Number 3 & 4  Same with "Sachin" and "Kapil" They Have Row Number 6 & 7]

SELECT firstname, lastname, salary, row_number() OVER (order by salary desc) AS row_num FROM employe;

+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
| firstname | lastname | salary | row_num |
+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
| rohit     | sharma   |  30000 |       1 |
| shikhar   | dhawan   |  25000 |       2 |
| shane     | warne    |  20000 |       3 |
| rahul     | dravid   |  20000 |       4 |
| saurabh   | ganguly  |  15000 |       5 |
| sachin    | sharma   |  10000 |       6 |
| kapil     | dev      |  10000 |       7 |
+-----------+----------+--------+---------+






-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------




B) RANK - [In This Same Row Number is Assign to the Records Which have Same Salary Like "shane" & "rahul" Both have Salary 20000 and they have Row Number 3 & 3  Same with "Sachin" and "Kapil" They Have 5 & 5]  

Note - [But Row Number 4 has been Skipped In this]

SELECT firstname, lastname, salary, RANK() OVER (order by salary desc) AS row_num FROM employe;

+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
| firstname | lastname | salary | row_num |
+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
| rohit     | sharma   |  30000 |       1 |
| shikhar   | dhawan   |  25000 |       2 |
| shane     | warne    |  20000 |       3 |
| rahul     | dravid   |  20000 |       3 |
| saurabh   | ganguly  |  15000 |       5 |
| sachin    | sharma   |  10000 |       6 |
| kapil     | dev      |  10000 |       6 |
+-----------+----------+--------+---------+







-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------



C) DENSE RANK - [In This Same Row Number is Assign to the Records Which have Same Salary Like "shane" & "rahul" Both have Salary 20000 and they have Row Number 3 & 3  Same with "Sachin" and "Kapil" They Have 5 & 5]

Note - [But Here 4 is Not Skipped]

SELECT firstname, lastname, salary, DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by salary desc) AS row_num FROM employe;

+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
| firstname | lastname | salary | row_num |
+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
| rohit     | sharma   |  30000 |       1 |
| shikhar   | dhawan   |  25000 |       2 |
| shane     | warne    |  20000 |       3 |
| rahul     | dravid   |  20000 |       3 |
| saurabh   | ganguly  |  15000 |       4 |
| sachin    | sharma   |  10000 |       5 |
| kapil     | dev      |  10000 |       5 |
+-----------+----------+--------+---------+
